Here's a complete implementation:

**XAML — wrap `CollectionView` in `RefreshView` for pull-to-refresh:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:models="clr-namespace:MyApp.Models"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ItemListPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ItemListViewModel">

    <RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
                 Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
        <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                        SelectionMode="Single"
                        SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                        SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}"
                        EmptyView="No items found.">
            <CollectionView.ItemsLayout>
                <LinearItemsLayout Orientation="Vertical"
                                   ItemSizingStrategy="MeasureFirstItem" />
            </CollectionView.ItemsLayout>
            <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
                <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                    <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                        <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                               WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                        <VerticalStackLayout Grid.Column="1"
                                             VerticalOptions="Center">
                            <Label Text="{Binding Name}"
                                   FontAttributes="Bold" />
                            <Label Text="{Binding Description}"
                                   FontSize="12"
                                   TextColor="Gray" />
                        </VerticalStackLayout>
                    </Grid>
                </DataTemplate>
            </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        </CollectionView>
    </RefreshView>
</ContentPage>
```

**ViewModel — using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm:**

```csharp
public partial class ItemListViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IItemService _itemService;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> _items = [];

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? _currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isRefreshing;

    public ItemListViewModel(IItemService itemService)
    {
        _itemService = itemService;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(
            $"{nameof(ItemDetailPage)}?id={CurrentItem.Id}");

        // Clear selection so re-selecting the same item works
        CurrentItem = null;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _itemService.GetItemsAsync();
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
            {
                Items = new ObservableCollection<Item>(data);
            });
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // stops the spinner
        }
    }
}
```

**Key binding relationships:**

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | Auto-updates UI on add/remove |
| `SelectedItem` (TwoWay) | `CurrentItem` | Tracks selection; set to `null` after navigation |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires navigation on tap |
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` | Set `false` when API call finishes to stop spinner |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Triggers data reload |

**Important details:**
- Always set `IsRefreshing = false` in a `finally` block — otherwise the spinner hangs on errors.
- Clear `CurrentItem = null` after navigating so the user can re-select the same item.
- Use `x:DataType` on both the page and `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- `MeasureFirstItem` improves scroll performance when items are uniform height.
